Pre-Game Insights: Experts predicted Australia as the favorites given their recent form and England's struggles in the tournament opener.
The Aussies have played 23 T20Is with the Aussies coming out on top in 10 occasions while England has won 11 of them.
England will be defending their T20 world champions title, while Australia will be the favourites to get the better of their rivals in their upcoming T20 World Cup 2024 match.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The pitch at the Kensington Oval in the T20 World Cup 2024 has provided assistance to the fast bowlers and spinners alike.
The average first innings score of 151 at this venue in T20Is could prove to be quite a competitive total when Australia takes on England in a high-octane clash.
Jos Buttler and Phil Salt will have the responsibility to provide quick starts in the powerplay overs for England.
Jofra Archer, who made his return to cricket for England after a long injury layoff, will be playing a key role of the enforcer.
Others: Australia squad for T20 World Cup 2024: Mitchell Marsh (c), Ashton Agar, Pat Cummins, Tim David, Nathan Ellis, Cameron Green, Josh Hazlewood, Travis Head, Josh Inglis, Glenn Maxwell, Mitchell Starc, Marcus Stoinis, Matthew Wade, David Warner, Adam Zampa

England squad for T20 World Cup 2024: Jos Buttler (c), Moeen Ali, Jofra Archer, Jonny Bairstow, Harry Brook, Sam Curran, Ben Duckett, Tom Hartley, Will Jacks, Chris Jordan, Liam Livingstone, Adil Rashid, Phil Salt, Reece Topley, Mark Wood
